  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1263497/files/CSB.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00001 Cartoons of the effective mass anomalous dimension $\gaEff(\la)$ in IR-conformal (left) and chirally-broken (right) continuum systems.  In both cases, \gaEff starts from zero at the asymptotically-free UV fixed point and increases as the energy decreases.  In IR-conformal systems, $\gaEff \to \ga_m^{\star}$ at the IRFP as $\la \to 0$.  At even stronger coupling \gaEff might increase with energy as suggested by the dashed blue line.  In chirally-broken systems the scaling form $\rho(\la) \propto \la^{\al(\la)}$ is lost below the chiral symmetry breaking scale.</subfield>
